<section class="border-t border-border-light/70 bg-charcoal py-20 dark:border-border-light/20" aria-label="The problem">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="reveal space-y-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white sm:text-3xl">AI is becoming the interface to everything.</h2>

      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-off-white/75">
        Not just search. Not just content. The answers you get, the options presented to you,
        the decisions you make&mdash;all increasingly flow through AI systems shaped by the
        incentives of the platforms that control them. Ads are showing up. Responses are being
        influenced. And unlike the old internet, you can't view source to see what's happening.
      </p>

      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-off-white/75">
        Right now, users have almost no way to see when something is being influenced,
        understand how outputs are being shaped, or set boundaries on what they will and won't accept.
      </p>

      <p class="text-base font-medium leading-relaxed text-cyan">
        adblocked.ai is a user-side layer that starts with what's obvious&mdash;ads&mdash;and
        builds toward giving you visibility and control over the rest.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
